{
  "text": "Similarly, it is yet not known whether protein products of the various identified TERT-, DKC1-, TINF2-, RTEL1 mutations per se lead to misfolding and accumulation in the ER and development of ER stress, as structural analyses of some of the above mentioned mutations predict beside impaired function a defective protein structure or reduced stability of the mutant proteins [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "5725852"
